HEADWORD: cesium
<hw>cesium</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>the chemical <isa>element</isa> of
atomic number 55. It is a univalent element, the most electropositive
metal. Symbol Cs; atomic weight 132.905. IT has a melting point of
28.4⟦deg⟧ C.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> caesium, Cs.</syn>⟦br⟧
